               <seg xml:id="C19_app7-#fThomas_start"/>have made me what I am.&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p335__End"/&gt;&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p336__Start"/&gt;“Spring advanced rapidly; the weather
            became fine, and the skies cloudless. It surprised me, that what before was desert and
            gloomy should now bloom with the most beautiful flowers and verdure. My senses were
            gratified and refreshed by a thousand scents of delight, and a thousand sights of
            beauty.&lt;p loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p336__End"/&gt;&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p337__Start"/&gt;“It was on one of these days, when my
            cottagers periodically rested from labour—the old man played on his guitar, and the
            children listened to <seg xml:id="C19_app7-#fThomas_end"/>
            
