               <seg xml:id="C19_app15-#fThomas_start"/>dismissing her guide, conducted her into the cottage. Some conversation
            took place between him and his father; and the young stranger knelt at the old man’s
            feet, and would have kissed his hand, but he raised her, and embraced her
            affectionately.&lt;p loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p339__End"/&gt;&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p340__Start"/&gt;“I soon perceived, that although the
            stranger uttered articulate sounds, and appeared to have a language of her own, she was
            neither understood by, <seg xml:id="C19_app15-#fThomas_end"/>
            
