               <seg type="invariant-MissingWit" xml:id="C19_app17-#fThomas_start"/>herself understood, the cottagers. They made many signs which I did not
            comprehend; but I saw that her presence diffused gladness through the cottage,
            dispelling their sorrow as the sun dissipates the morning mists. Felix seemed peculiarly
            happy, and with smiles of delight welcomed his Arabian. Agatha, the ever-gentle Agatha,
            kissed the hands of the lovely stranger; and, pointing to her brother, made signs which
            appeared to me to mean that he had been sorrowful until she came. Some hours passed
            thus, while they, by their countenances, expressed joy, the cause of which I did not
            comprehend. Presently I found, by the frequent recurrence of <seg xml:id="C19_app17-#fThomas_end"/>
            
