               <seg xml:id="C19_app33-#fThomas_start"/>the decline of that mighty empire; of chivalry, Christianity, and kings.
            I heard of the discovery of the American hemisphere, and wept with Safie over the
            hapless fate of its original inhabitants.&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p348__End"/&gt;&lt;p
            loc="novel1_letter4_chapter12_p349__Start"/&gt;“These wonderful narrations inspired me
            with strange feelings. Was man, indeed, at once so powerful, so virtuous, and
            magnificent, yet so vicious and base? He appeared at one time a mere scion of the evil
            principle, and at <seg xml:id="C19_app33-#fThomas_end"/>
            
